Now that the multinationals have gone to court, we can only wait to see what the next steps will be but whatever the outcome, it is important to have a policy framework that will improve earnings for all players, especially the smallholders numbering about 500,000.
At the beginning of the year, fresh produce associations lamented about the proposed laws on the Horticulture Development Authority as the ministry seeks to once again separate the firms that were collapsed to form the Agriculture and Food Authority. The organisations have called for a postponement of new tax laws arguing the sector, which has been hit hard by the outbreak of Covid-19, needs time to recover from losses and markets disruption.
From these two examples, it is obvious there is need for stakeholder engagement in policy framework formulation for development of regulations that enable players to move forward together. Smallholder maize farmers in Tanzania have organised themselves into group through which they sell thousands of tonnes to Kenyan millers in search of the best prices. The region has potential to produce 25,000 tonnes of mangoes and 20,000 tonnes of passion fruits annually, He warns the opposition that any attempt to disrupt social order will be dealt with decisively. For Kenya, Mr Museveni could be a major behind-the-scenes player in President Uhuru Kenyatta’s succession campaigns. His closest rival Robert Kyagulanyi, aka Bobi Wine, came second with 38.4 per cent of the votes cast.